The paper proposes a deep learning model for identifying structure within experiment narratives in scientific literature. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically, discourse analysis. The model is a Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) with Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) cells that labels clauses, which is a common approach in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

The paper also involves attention mechanisms and information extraction, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning) are also likely sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper involves analyzing scientific literature, which is a common topic in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely sub-category.
